<item>
            <title>[JDK-8350260] Improve HTML instruction formatting in PassFailJFrame</title>
                <link>https://bugs.openjdk.org/browse/JDK-8350260</link>
                <project id="10100" key="JDK">JDK</project>
                    <description>When instructions are long, the formatting in PassFailJFrame looks off:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
1. When the instructions are displayed on the screen, the HTML is scrolled to the bottom, which isn&amp;#39;t convenient;&lt;br/&gt;
2. Numbers above 10 in the list are clipped on the left;&lt;br/&gt;
3. No border around the HTML text.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
These problems were found while converting the instructions for test/jdk/javax/accessibility/TestJCheckBoxToggleAccessibility.java in code review [1][2] for &lt;a href=&quot;https://bugs.openjdk.org/browse/JDK-8348936&quot; title=&quot;[Accessibility,macOS,VoiceOver] VoiceOver doesn&amp;#39;t announce untick on toggling the checkbox with &amp;quot;space&amp;quot; key on macOS&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;JDK-8348936&quot;&gt;&lt;strike&gt;JDK-8348936&lt;/strike&gt;&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=&quot;https://bugs.openjdk.org/browse/JDK-8345728&quot; title=&quot;[Accessibility,macOS,Screen Magnifier]: JCheckbox unchecked state does not magnify but works for checked state&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;JDK-8345728&quot;&gt;&lt;strike&gt;JDK-8345728&lt;/strike&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
[1] &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/openjdk/jdk/pull/23436&quot;&gt;https://github.com/openjdk/jdk/pull/23436&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
[2] &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/openjdk/jdk/pull/23436#discussion_r1953131477&quot;&gt;https://github.com/openjdk/jdk/pull/23436#discussion_r1953131477&lt;/a&gt;</description>
